/pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/dimpled-koala-fossil-found-western-australia-revealed-why-previously-unknown-species-died-out-180988719/</guid></item><item><title>昆虫能感觉到疼痛吗？新研究表明蟋蟀确实如此</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-insects-feel-pain-new-research-suggests-that-crickets-do-180988752/</link><description>这些生物用于食物、饲料和研究，是养殖最广泛的昆虫之一。研究作者表示，人类应该努力减少昆虫养殖、处理和实验中的危害</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-insects-feel-pain-new-research-suggests-that-crickets-do-180988752/</guid></item><item><title>随着华盛顿地标建筑继续庆祝其成立 50 周年，这些色彩缤纷的当代艺术品加入了赫希霍恩博物馆的收藏</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-colorful-contemporary-artworks-just-joined-the-hirshhorn-museum-as-the-dc-landmark-celebrated-its-50th-anniversary-180988749/</link><description>该博物馆还准备于今年秋天重新开放其重新设计的雕塑花园，展出八位艺术家的新作品</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 15:00:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-colorful-contemporary-artworks-just-joined-the-hirshhorn-museum-as-the-dc-landmark-celebrated-its-50th-anniversary-180988749/</guid></item><item><title>座头鲸有时会无缘无故地张开嘴。游客正在帮助科学家了解这种罕见的行为</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humpback-whales-sometimes-hold-their-mouths-open-for-no-clear-reason-tourists-are-helping-scientists-understand-the-rare-behavior-180988743/</link><description>从社交媒体收集的大量照片和视频帮助研究人员提出了这种很少被记录的动作（称为“张开嘴”）的一些可能原因，包括沟通、下巴伸展和玩耍</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humpback-whales-sometimes-hold-their-mouths-open-for-no-clear-reason-tourists-are-helping-scientists-understand-the-rare-behavior-180988743/</guid></item><item><title>碧昂丝和泰勒·斯威夫特的音乐以及数十首其他“音频宝藏”已添加到国家唱片登记处</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</link><description>美国国会图书馆国家播放列表中最新添加的 25 首歌曲被认为“因其在国家录制的声音遗产中的文化、历史或美学重要性而值得永远保存”</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 21:32:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</guid></item><item><title>在巨大的铁器时代宝藏中发现了英国部落强大女王可能使用过的“神奇”镜子，目前正在展出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</link><description>参观约克郡博物馆的游客可以看到来自梅尔森比宝库的文物，其历史可以追溯到公元一世纪，这些文物改写了罗马入侵时期英国财富和权力的故事</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 20:44:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</guid></item><item><title>无意识意识是否意识到周围的环境？新研究表明麻醉大脑可以处理无意中听到的单词</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</link><description>七名参与者的电极暂时植入对学习很重要的大脑结构中。在麻醉状态下，他们的神经细胞学会了区分不同的声音，甚至可以预测短语中即将出现的单词</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:40:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</guid></item><item><title>新的稀有鸽子幼崽是已灭绝野生鸟类的“希望之源”，也是拯救它们的雄心勃勃的计划向前迈出的一步</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</link><description>自 1972 年以来，索科罗斑鸠就没有在野外记录过，但环保人士表示，由于长期的重新引入努力，这种情况可能会在短短几年内发生变化</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:07:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</guid></item></channel></rss>